adjectives.description: gasproof (comparative more gasproof, superlative most gasproof)

entries.meaning: Made of or covered with material that doesn't allow gas in.
examples: Made of oiled silk, a gasproof suit that can be packed into a pouch and carried in a handbag offers protection from gas to a person caught in an air raid.
Fabrics needed to be lightweight, gasproof, and strong.
